<h2>FAQs About Buffalo Wild Wings' Parmesan Garlic Sauce</h2>

<div class="faq">
    <h3>1. Is Buffalo Wild Wings' Parmesan Garlic Sauce gluten-free?</h3>
    <p>Yes, according to Buffalo Wild Wings' allergen menu, the Parmesan Garlic Sauce is listed as gluten-free. However, always verify with the restaurant staff to ensure there have been no changes in the recipe or preparation process.</p>

    <h3>2. Are there any gluten-containing ingredients in the Parmesan Garlic Sauce?</h3>
    <p>The primary ingredients in the Parmesan Garlic Sauce, such as Parmesan cheese, garlic, butter, mayonnaise, and spices, do not contain gluten. However, cross-contamination can occur in the kitchen, so it's essential to communicate your dietary needs to the staff.</p>

    <h3>3. What other gluten-free options are available at Buffalo Wild Wings?</h3>
    <p>Buffalo Wild Wings offers several gluten-free options, including Mild Sauce, Medium Sauce, Hot Sauce, Caribbean Jerk Sauce, and Naked Tenders. Always check the allergen menu for the most up-to-date information.</p>

    <h3>4. How does Buffalo Wild Wings prevent cross-contamination?</h3>
    <p>Buffalo Wild Wings takes precautions to minimize cross-contamination, but their kitchens are not entirely gluten-free. It is recommended to inform the staff of your dietary restrictions and inquire about their specific measures to prevent cross-contamination.</p>
</div>

<h2>Conclusion</h2>

<p>Buffalo Wild Wings' Parmesan Garlic Sauce is listed as gluten-free on their allergen menu, making it a suitable option for individuals with gluten sensitivities or celiac disease. However, it is crucial to remain vigilant about potential cross-contamination in the kitchen. By communicating your dietary needs to the restaurant staff and staying informed about the ingredients and preparation methods, you can enjoy your meal with confidence. Buffalo Wild Wings continues to expand its gluten-free offerings, providing a variety of options for those who need to avoid gluten. Always check the latest allergen information and consult with the staff to ensure a safe dining experience.</p>

